title: AlphaTALKS Wall Street Breakfast August 7: What Moved Markets This Week
author: Seeking Alpha
dc:creator: Seeking Alpha
description: Stocks gained some ground this week as employment figures showed the U.S. economy continuing to gain steam. Initial jobless claims declined and the insured unemployment rate fell while today's non-farm payrolls report beat expectations. The unemployment rate fell to 5.4%, a post-pandemic low.
